  "meta": {
    "bfsk_grid_note": "BFSK sampled at 3-4 SNR levels x 3 distances (vs 5x3 for MFSK) because BFSK collapses completely (BER~0.495, corr_peak~0.277) even at best acoustic conditions (0.5m, 30dB SNR). SNR sweep is irrelevant: failure is reverb-driven, not noise-driven.",
    "key_finding": "Both modems fail completely (clean_decode_prob=0.00) at ALL tested conditions. Sync acquisition (corr_peak) is the bottleneck: 0.277 for BFSK and 0.297 for MFSK at 0.5m (both below ~0.6 viable threshold). 3x repetition coding does not help \u2014 BER actually increases slightly because the demodulator is fed 3x more corrupted output to majority-vote over when sync is already lost. The failure mode is reverb-induced sync loss, not ambient noise or distance per se.",
    "reference_P3_smoke": "P3 (acoustic_close_quiet, 0.15m, 30dB pink) from smoketest: bfsk_b0 corr_peak=0.414, P4 (far noisy, 0.5m, babble) corr_peak=0.277. Even P3 was below viable threshold \u2014 P4 is harder still."
  }
